AB  - The proceedings contain 296 papers. The topics discussed include: multidimensional load-pull extrapolation for accelerated computer-aided design (CAD) simulations; design of a decade-bandwidth tunable multi-notch filter for RFI mitigation in a congested spectral environment; hybrid quantum-classical algorithms for satellite swarm optimization in non-terrestrial networks; development of an all-dielectric quantum-based RF field sensor for electric field calibrations; dynamics of quantized signals in random media: a transport theoretic model; performance showdown: Rydberg sensors vs. electrically small antennas; towards harsh environment silicon carbide based on-chip antenna; cylindrical dielectric resonator antenna providing pattern diversity using higher-order modes; and direct antenna binary phase-shift keying through ferrimagnetic loading.
