AB  - The proceedings contain 30 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Artificial Life and Evolutionary Computation. The topics include: How to Turn a Leaky Learner into a Sealed One; capturing Emerging Complexity in Lenia; on the Detection of Significant Pairwise Interactions in Complex Systems; the Properties of Pseudo-Attractors in Random Boolean Networks; analysing the Expressiveness of Metabolic Networks Representations; scFBApy: A Python Framework for Super-Network Flux Balance Analysis; semantic Information as a Measure of Synthetic Cells’ Knowledge of the Environment; General Lines, Routes and Perspectives of Wetware Embodied AI. From Its Organizational Bases to a Glimpse on Social Chemical Robotics; a Proposed Mechanism for in vivo Programming Transmembrane Receptors; kauffman Model with Spatially Separated Ligation and Cleavage Reactions; percolation Breakdown in Binary and Ternary Monodisperse and Polydisperse Systems of Spherical Particles; entangled Gondolas. Design of Multi-layer Networks of Quantum-Driven Robotic Swarms; generalizations of Evolved Decision-Making Mechanisms in Swarm Collective Perception; an Investigation of Graceful Degradation in Boolean Network Robots Subject to Online Adaptation; Blockchain-Empowered PSO for Scalable Swarm Robotics; Hybrid GP/PSO Representation of 1-D Signals in an Autoencoder Fashion; local Delay Plasticity Supports Generalized Learning in Spiking Neural Networks; Improving PVC Detection in ECG Signals: A Recurrent Neural Network Approach; clustering Trajectories to Study Diabetic Kidney Disease; Multi-classification of Alzheimer’s Disease by NSGA-II Slices Optimization and Fusion Deep Learning; Exploiting the Potential of Bayesian Networks in Deriving New Insight into Diabetic Kidney Disease (DKD); a Genetic Algorithm for Feature Selection for Alzheimer’s Disease Detection Using a Deep Transfer Learning Approach; learning Whether to be Informed in an Agent-Based Evolutionary Market Model; heterogeneous Mean-Field Analysis of Best-of-n Decision Making in Networks with Zealots; does ‘Community Detection’ Find Real Emerging Meso-structures? A Statistical Test Based on Complex Networks Methods; self-loops in Social Networks: Behavior of Eigenvector Centrality; evolutionary Story Sifting over the Log of a Social Simulation.
