AB  - The proceedings contain 24 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Annual Meeting of the Bulgarian Section of the Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics. The topics include: Live-Graphing with LoRaWAN and Python; quantified Formulation of an Interval Model in Mechanics; Numerical Methods for Fractional Diffusion-Reaction Problems Based on Operator Splitting and BURA; preface; analysis of Contaminant Removal in a Constructed Wetland Operating Under Step-Feeding: A Monte Carlo Based Stochastic Treatment Accounting for Uncertainty; new Ant Colony Optimization Including Weights; improvement of Air Pollution Caused by Traffic Through Different Signal Timing Policies – Case Study of Sofia; sensitivity Study of a Large-Scale Air Pollution Model by Using Latin Hypercube Sampling; quantum Effects on Dislocation Motion in Pure and Hydrogen Charged Fe from Ring-Polymer Molecular Dynamics; reconstruction of Time-Dependent Implied Volatility by Market Observations for European Options in Jump–Diffusion Models; statistical Properties of Stationary Flow of Substance in a Network Channel Containing Arbitrary Number of Arms; the c0- Analytic Semigroup of Contractions, Generated by a Kind of Timoshenko Beam Type Dirichlet Boundary Operator; chaotic Behaviour in a Generalized Model of Three Competing Economic Sectors; axisymmetric Oscillatory Flow of Carreau Fluid in Tube; exponential Difference Scheme Approximations for Unsaturated Flow Equation with Piecewise Constant or Degenerate Absolute Permeability; computing Reliable Solutions of Chaotic Dynamical Systems Using Multiple-precision Arithmetic; characterization of Porous Materials by Homogenization Models Based on a Generalized Mixture Rule; solar Radiation Modelling for Bulgaria Based on Assimilated Surface Data; ETCCDI Thermal Climate Indices in the CMIP5 Future Climate Projections over Southeast Europe; inuitionistic Fuzzy Anova Approach to the Management of Movie Sales Revenue; quasi-Monte Carlo Methods Based on Low Discrepancy Sequences for Sensitivity Analysis in Air Pollution Modelling; Effects of Satellite Data Assimilation on Air Quality Parameters Simulated by the Bulgarian Chemical Weather Forecast System (BgCWFS).
