AB  - The proceedings contain 166 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Artificial Intelligence and Security. The topics include: Community Detection Based on Topology and Node Features in Social Networks; Development of Intelligent Integrated Energy System Based on MVC; study on IoT Big Data Direction in Civil Aviation; evaluation of the Impact of Haze with Uncertain Probabilistic Linguistic Term Sets; research on the Application of Ant Colony Clustering in Commodity Classification; Prediction of the Total Phosphorus Index Based on ARIMA; single Platform Passive Location Algorithm Using Position Information and Azimuth; research on Regional Development Efficiency and Influencing Factors of China’s Ocean Energy Equipment Manufacturing; EAC-GAN: Semi-supervised Image Enhancement Technology to Improve CNN Classification Performance; a Comprehensive Utilization Model of Informationization Teaching Resources; SRPAIS: Spectral Matching Algorithm Based on Raman Peak Alignment and Intensity Selection; a Semantic Representation Scheme for Medical Dispute Judgment Documents Based on Elements Extraction; study on the Portrait of Online Learners’ Personality and Attitude; research on Resilience Cloud Environment Capability Evaluation System Under Complex Cyber Threat; a New Stock Forecasting Model by Hidden Quantum Markov Models; review of Detection and Avoidance of Interference Among Multiple Applications in Software-Defined Networks; intelligent Optimization Method of Microservice Redeployment for Communication Power Supply and Computer Room Environment Monitoring Platform; DCAL: A New Method for Defending Against Adversarial Examples; Test Traffic Control Based on REST API for Software-Defined Networking; A Study of Heterogeneous Database Integration Based on Web Service and XML; formal Verification of Security Protocols: ProVerif and Extensions; secure Evaluation of Discrete Sine Transform in Homomorphic Encrypted Domain; efficient and Secure Outsourced Image 