AB  - The proceedings contain 50 papers. The special focus in this conference is on  Supercomputing. The topics include: Implementation of Discrete Element Method to the Simulation of Solid Materials Fracturing; information Entropy Initialized Concrete Autoencoder for Optimal Sensor Placement and Reconstruction of Geophysical Fields; microwave Radiometric Mapping of Broken Cumulus Cloud Fields from Space: Numerical Simulations; parallel Computations by the Grid-Characteristic Method on Chimera Computational Grids in 3D Problems of Railway Non-destructive Testing; parallel Computing in Solving the Problem of Interval Multicriteria Optimization in Chemical Kinetics; parallel Efficiency for Poroelasticity; parallel Implementation of Fast 3D Travel Time Tomography for Depth-Velocity Model Building in Seismic Exploration Problems; parallel Implementation of Multioperators-Based Scheme of the 16-th Order for Three-Dimensional Calculation of the Jet Flows; parallel Implementation of the Seismic Sources Recovery in Randomly Heterogeneous Media; analysis and Elimination of Bottlenecks in Parallel Algorithm for Solving Global Optimization Problems; Performance Analysis of GPU-Based Code for Complex Plasma Simulation; PIConGPU on Desmos Supercomputer: GPU Acceleration, Scalability and Storage Bottleneck; Quasi-one-Dimensional Polarized Superfluids: A DMRG Study; Sintering Simulation Using GPU-Based Algorithm for the Samples with a Large Number of Grains; software Package for High-Performance Computations in Airframe Assembly Modeling; State-of-the-Art Molecular Dynamics Packages for GPU Computations: Performance, Scalability and Limitations; supercomputer Simulations of Turbomachinery Problems with Higher Accuracy on Unstructured Meshes; Validation of Quantum-Chemical Methods with the New COSMO2 Solvent Model; data-Based Choice of the Training Dataset for the Numerical Dispersion Mitigation Neural Network; deep Machine Learning Investigation of Phase Transitions; analysis of P