AB  - To tackle the train sepevration optimization problem between station sections in high-speed railways with moving block signaling system, this paper adopted the "blocking time stairways" model based on fixed blocking systems to construct "time space occupation band" optimization model in moving block signaling system. Firstly, the train operation process between stations was decomposed, to acquire the four types of speeds within eight phases that affect the train sectional operation, namely the station throat exit speed, sectional cruising speed, terminal coasting speed and station throat entry speed. In the meantime, the minimum headway between trains was analyzed based on departure headway, sectional headway, and arrival headway. Then, this paper analyzed the train following process by the upper-lower-bound of "time space occupation band" and constructed the train following model that minimizes the energy consumption and operation time. This model was solved using the quantum evolutionary algorithm to optimize the train departure headways and the sectional following strategy. Finally, a case study of the CRH380AL EMU, and Chibi North-Yueyang East of Wuhan-Guangzhou railway as simulation section verified the effectiveness of moving block "time-space occupation band" and quantum evolutionary algorithm. © 2021, Department of Journal of the China Railway Society. All right reserved.
