AB  - The proceedings contain 27 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Intelligent Computing and Networking. The topics include: Exploiting Processor Variability for Efficient Application Mapping; data Sharing Over the Cloud Based on Ring Signature; data Analytics on Columnar Databases in Big Data Environment; real Time Multiple Object Detection on Low-Constrained Devices using Lightweight Deep Neural Network; Researcher Framework Using MongoDB and FCM Clustering for Prediction of the Future of Patients from EHR; performance Level Evaluation of Cryptographic Algorithms; driver Activity Monitoring Using MobileNets; a Review of Deep Learning Techniques Used in Breast Cancer Image Classification; Prediction of nMAG in PMIPv6 with the Help of MN Positions; surveillance System for Intruder Detection Using Facial Recognition; clinical Risk Prediction of Acute Coronary Syndrome Using Deep Learning Approach; genetic Algorithm for Feature Selection and Parameter Optimization to Enhance Learning on Framingham Heart Disease Dataset; securing IoT Devices Generated Data Using Homomorphic Encryption; Secure Data Aggregation and Data Transmission Using HMAC Protocol in Cluster Base Wireless Sensor Network; performance Evaluation of Adversarial Examples on Deep Neural Network Architectures; study on Analysis of Gene Expression Dataset and Identification of Differentially Expressed Genes; A Modified EDDKA Routing Approach to Enhance Quality of Service (QoS)-Enabled Data Dissemination in VANETs; a Novel and Secure Approach for Quantum Key Distribution in a Cloud Computing Environment; voting Using Blockchain Technology; deepfake Detection Approaches Using Deep Learning: A Systematic Review; secured Crowdfunding Platform Using Blockchain; review of Wireless Sensor Network Security Schemes; development of Agriculture Field Using Machine Learning.
