AB  - In view of the problems of low load rate of single vehicle and low average daily transfer rate in traditional optimization methods for the vehicle distribution path of multi-temperature co-distribution cold chain logistics due to the ignorance of interfering factors in each distribution stage, a novel optimization method for the vehicle distribution path of multi-temperature co-distribution cold chain logistics was proposed. Under the premise of considering the interfering factors, e.g., distribution time of multi-temperature cold chain logistics, distribution cost and distribution risks, an optimization model for the vehicle distribution path of multi-temperature co-distribution cold chain logistics was established, and the multi-objective optimization problem was simplified into a single-objective optimization problem. Quantum bits were used to describe the relevant information of distribution path, and an ant colony algorithm was used to solve the optimal path of optimization model so as to realize the path optimization. The results show that the load rate and average daily transfer rate of as-proposed method increase by 29.3% and 22.8%, respectively. © 2021, Editorial Department of Journal of Shenyang University of Technology. All right reserved.
