AB  - The proceedings contain 55 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Supercomputing Days. The topics include: Quantum Software Engineering: Quantum Gate-Based Computational Intelligence Supremacy; privacy-Preserving Logistic Regression as a Cloud Service Based on Residue Number System; parallel Box-Counting Method for Evaluating the Fractal Dimension of Analytically Defined Curves; Parallel BIILU2-Based Iterative Solution of Linear Systems in Reservoir Simulation: Do Optimal Parameters Exist?; optimization of Load Balancing Algorithms in Parallel Modeling of Objects Using a Large Number of Grids; solving the Problem of Texture Images Classification Using Synchronous Distributed Deep Learning on Desktop Grid Systems; running Many-Task Applications Across Multiple Resources with Everest Platform; risky Search with Increasing Complexity by a Desktop Grid; replication of “Tail” Computations in a Desktop Grid Project; enumerating the Orthogonal Diagonal Latin Squares of Small Order for Different Types of Orthogonality; New Compact Streaming in LBM with ConeFold LRnLA Algorithms; discrete Event Simulation Model of a Desktop Grid System; Development of Experimental Data Processing Workflows Based on Kubernetes Infrastructure and REANA Workflow Management System; availability-Based Resources Allocation Algorithms in Distributed Computing; Tuning ANNs Hyperparameters and Neural Architecture Search Using HPC; The Algorithms Properties and Structure Study as a Mandatory Element of Modern IT Education; students’ Favorite Parallel Programming Practices; Shared Memory Based MPI Broadcast Algorithms for NUMA Systems; set Classification in Set@l Language for Architecture-Independent Programming of High-Performance Computer Systems; Multiple-Precision BLAS Library for Graphics Processing Units; research of Hardware Implementations Efficiency of Sorting Algorithms Created by Using Xilinx’s High-Level Synthesis Tool; preface.
