AB  - The proceedings contain 47 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Cellular Automata for Research and Industry. The topics include: Towards Self-organizing Sensor Networks: Game-Theoretic e-Learning Automata-Based Approach; Termination and Stability Levels in Evolved CA Agents for the Black–Pattern Task; size Effect in Cellular Automata Based Disease Spreading Model; pheromone Interactions in a Cellular Automata-Based Model for Surveillance Robots; Agent-Based Simulation of Information Spreading in VANET; analysis of Rates of Agents’ Decisions in Learning to Cross a Highway in Populations with Risk Takers and Risk Avoiders; The Automatic Generation of an Efficient Floor Field for CA Simulations in Crowd Management; traffic on Small Grids and the Ramp Problem; the Impact of Different Angle Paths on Discrete-Continuous Pedestrian Dynamics Model; modeling Spatio-Temporal Dynamics of Metabolic Networks with Cellular Automata and Constraint-Based Methods; two-Way Road Cellular Automaton Model with Loading/Unloading Bays for Traffic Flow Simulation; A Microscopic CA Model of Traffic Flow?; regional Control of Probabilistic Cellular Automata; regional Synchronization of a Probabilistic Cellular Automaton; Firsts Steps in Cellular Fields Optimization: A FSSP Case Study; Implementations of FSSP Algorithms on Fault-Tolerant Cellular Arrays; do There Exist Non-linear Maximal Length Cellular Automata? A Study; polynomial Equations over Finite, Discrete-Time Dynamical Systems; the Representation Role for Basic Operations Embodied in Cellular Automata: A Suitability Example for Addition in Redundant Numeral Systems vs Conventional Ones; quantum Walks on Quantum Cellular Automata Lattices: Towards a New Model for Quantum Computation; a Novel Cellular Automata Modelling Framework for Micro-environmental Interaction and Co-invasion; self-verifying Cellular Automata.
