AB  - The proceedings contain 39 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Mobile Ad-hoc and Sensor Networks. The topics include: Achieving communication effectiveness of web authentication protocol with key update; placement fraud detection on smart phones: A joint crowdsourcing and data analyzing based approach; a reinforcement learning approach of data forwarding in vehicular networks; privacy-assured large-scale navigation from encrypted approximate shortest path recommendation; an efficient and secure authentication scheme for in-vehicle networks in connected vehicle; research of task scheduling mechanism based on prediction of memory utilization; an effective method for community search in large directed attributed graphs; EPAF: An efficient pseudonymous-based inter-vehicle authentication framework for VANET; CHAR-HMM: An improved continuous human activity recognition algorithm based on hidden markov model; Receive buffer pre-division based flow control for MPTCP; a prediction method based on complex event processing for cyber physical system; A fast handover scheme for SDN based vehicular network; secret-sharing approach for detecting compromised mobile sink in unattended wireless sensor networks; understanding trajectory data based on heterogeneous information network using visual analytics; automatic prediction of traffic flow based on deep residual networks; trust mechanism based aodv routing protocol for forward node authentication in mobile ad hoc network; hybrid quantum-behaved particle swarm optimization for mobile-edge computation offloading in internet of things; enhancing software reliability against soft error using critical data model; APDL: A practical privacy-preserving deep learning model for smart devices; barrier coverage lifetime maximization in a randomly deployed bistatic radar network; Gesture recognition system based on RFID.
