AB  - The proceedings contain 104 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Pioneer Computer Scientists, Engineers and Educators. The topics include: Meteorological Sensor Data Storage Mechanism Based on TimescaleDB and Kafka; cost Optimization Strategy for Long-Term Storage of Scientific Workflow; optimal Overbooking Mechanism in Data Plan Sharing; survey of Data Value Evaluation Methods Based on Open Source Scientific and Technological Information; Credible Routing Scheme of SDN-Based Cloud Using Blockchain; integrated Multi-featured Android Malicious Code Detection; computation Offloading Algorithms in Mobile Edge Computing System: A Survey; wireless Communication Signal Strength Prediction Method Based on the K-nearest Neighbor Algorithm; prediction Model for Non-topological Event Propagation in Social Networks; interest-Forgetting Markov Model for Next-Basket Recommendation; Experimental Research on Internet Ecosystem and AS Hierarchy; speed-Grading Mobile Charging Policy in Large-Scale Wireless Rechargeable Sensor Networks; Solar Radio Burst Automatic Detection Method for Decimetric and Metric Data of YNAO; internet Web Trust System Based on Smart Contract; destructive Method with High Quality and Speed to Counter Information Hiding; defence Against Adversarial Attacks Using Clustering Algorithm; A Privacy-Preserving TPA-aided Remote Data Integrity Auditing Scheme in Clouds; relation Extraction Based on Dual Attention Mechanism; analysis and Defense of Network Attacking Based on the Linux Server; Anti-quantum Cryptography Scheme Based on the Improvement of Cubic Simple Matrix and LRPC Code; attention Neural Network for User Behavior Modeling; survey on Blockchain Incentive Mechanism; blockchain-Based Secure Authentication Scheme for Medical Data Sharing; Encryption Algorithm Based NTRU in Underwater Acoustic Networks; knowledge-Enhanced Bilingual Textual Representations for Cross-Lingual Semantic Textual Similarity.
