AB  - The proceedings contain 56 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Computational Intelligence and Its Applications. The topics include: A New Handwritten Signature Verification System Based on the Histogram of Templates Feature and the Joint Use of the Artificial Immune System with SVM; improved Quantum Chaotic Animal Migration Optimization Algorithm for QoS Multicast Routing Problem; developing a Conceptual Framework for Software Evolution Methods via Architectural Metrics; a Study on Self-adaptation in the Evolutionary Strategy Algorithm; swarm Intelligence Algorithm for Microwave Filter Optimization; innovation Diffusion in Social Networks: A Survey; an Efficient Cooperative Method to Solve Multiple Sequence Alignment Problem; automatic Ontology Learning from Heterogeneous Relational Databases: Application in Alimentation Risks Field; towards the Prediction of Multiple Soft-Biometric Characteristics from Handwriting Analysis; basketball Analytics. Data Mining for Acquiring Performances; gearbox Fault Diagnosis Based on Mel-Frequency Cepstral Coefficients and Support Vector Machine; a Modified Firefly Algorithm with Support Vector Machine for Medical Data Classification; ensemble Learning for Large Scale Virtual Screening on Apache Spark; Trace Based System in TEL Systems: Theory and Practice; using a Social-Based Collaborative Filtering with Classification Techniques; flexibility in Classification Process; an Evolutionary Scheme for Improving Recommender System Using Clustering; drug-Target Interaction Prediction in Drug Repositioning Based on Deep Semi-Supervised Learning; FA-SETPOWER-MRTA: A Solution for Solving the Multi-Robot Task Allocation Problem; effective Streaming Evolutionary Feature Selection Using Dynamic Optimization; similarity Measures for Spatial Clustering; Evolutionary Multi-objective Optimization of Business Process Designs with MA-NSGAII; sink Mobility Based on Bacterial Foraging Optimization Algorithm.
