AB  - The proceedings contain 30 papers. The topics discussed include: adaptive routing and spectrum assignment in flexgrid optical networks; sustainability in photonics – an introduction; optical flexibility – a router point of view; coexistence of PSK quantum key distribution and WDM in optical transmission systems; comparison of wavelength-routed and wavelength-split WDM-PON in mobile x-haul in dense urban areas; how to design an optimized set of fiber- trees for filterless optical networks – the elegance of a multi-goal evolutionary Pareto optimization versus a brute-force approach; evaluation of crosstalk attacks in access networks; efficient partial recovery of flexible-rate transceivers with SDN-based asymmetric multipath routing of IP traffic; and virtualization in high-throughput network elements and its impact on energy consumption.
