AB  - The proceedings contain 80  papers. The topics discussed include: a simulation optimization method for design and control of signalized intersections in urban areas; use of CPANS for grouping DNA sequence fragments in the construction of gnomes; analysing collaborative performance and cost allocation for the joint route planning problem; influence of manufacturing process in mechanical behavior of injected plastic components; use of games to student training in the civil engineering undergraduation course: a bibliometric analysis; quantum cognition models of ethical decision-making in human behavior simulation; simulation model of prefabricated house from manufacturing to on-site installation; a hybrid simulation-based optimization approach for scheduling dynamic block assembly in shipbuilding; educational animation as a complementary tool to convey knowledge to civil construction workers; agent-based micro simulation to assess the performance of roundabouts considering different variables and performance indicators; simulation and optimization with GRASP in supply fuel in the north of Mexico city; synchronization algorithm for peer-to-peer interactive distributed simulation implemented in a single-threaded web application; evidence-based evaluation of psychosocial risk factors and the interaction of their stressors using system dynamics; des techniques applied to the design of a training session about lean methodology in a shipbuilding process; theory and practice of information fusion models� quality estimation and models� quality control; and using simulation and reliability concepts to set starting times in multitask projects with random duration and a common deadline.
