AB  - The proceedings contain 47 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Automation Control Theory Perspectives in Intelligent Systems. The topics include: A novel color image encryption algorithm using chaotic map and improved RC4; modified discrete LQ control algorithm for situations with the scan period variance; polynomial approximation of quasipolynomials based on digital filter design principles; an implementation of a tilt-compensated eCompass; calibration of triaxial accelerometer and triaxial magnetometer for tilt compensated electronic compass; single scheduling variable approach; inverted pendulum optimal control based on first principle model; a cross-layer routing metric for multihop wireless networks; mean square stability and dissipativity of split-step theta method for stochastic delay differential equations with poisson white noise excitations; nonlinearity and time-delay compensations in state-space model based predictive control; plant-wide control of a reactive distillation column on biodiesel production; state-space predictive control of two liquid tanks system; quantum evolutionary cellular automata mapping optimization technique targeting regular network on chip; development of a set of applications for intelligent control system of compressor facilities at an industrial enterprise; simulation approach for optimal maintenance intervals estimation of electronic devices; scanning system for ballistic analysis; predictive-based stochastic modelling of power transmission system for leveraging fault tolerance; a matlab program for analysis of robust stability under parametric uncertainty; FPGA based self-tuning PI controller using IFT technique; design and implementation of an integrated system with secure encrypted data transmission and web application for simple system identification from experimental data.
