AB  - The proceedings contain 57 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Intelligent Decision Technologies. The topics include: A cloud-based vegetable production and distribution system; capacity planning in non-uniform depth anchorages; automatic image classification for the urinoculture screening; comparing hybrid metaheuristics for the bus driver rostering problem; effective stopping rule for population-based cooperative search approach to the vehicle routing problem; a rule based framework for smart training using SEMG signal; distributed speech recognition for lighting system control; an experimental study of scenarios for the agent-based RBF network design; eye movements data processing for Ab initio military pilot training; massive-scale gaze analytics exploiting high performance computing; a simulation approach to select interoperable solutions in supply chain dyads; dealing with seasonality while forecasting urban water demand; possibilistic very fast decision tree for uncertain data streams; detection of variations in holter ECG recordings based on dynamic cluster analysis; a theoretical framework for trusted communication; design requirements to integrate eye trackers in simulation environments; human friendly associative classifiers for early childhood caries; QOS-aware web service composition using quantum inspired particle swarm optimization; distance-based ensemble online classifier with kernel clustering; towards a new approach for an effective querying of distributed databases; the eye tracking methods in user interfaces assessment; using non-calibrated eye movement data to enhance human computer interfaces and a study on composition of elements for AHP.
