AB  - Focusing on the nonlinearity and the proved chaotic characteristic of traffic flow, the paper proposes a short-term traffic flow forecasting method based on phase space reconstruction and optimized RBF neural network (RBFNN). Firstly, the paper uses the K-means clustering algorithm to determine the center vector and width of hidden layer in RBFNN, then the quantum-behaved particle swarm optimization (QPSO) algorithm with global search capability is introduced to obtain the connection weight of network, and finally the paper reconstructs the phase space of measured traffic flow data which will be taken as the input sample of the optimized RBFNN. Simulation results have demonstrated the feasibility of the proposed traffic flow forecasting metho d, and the forecasting precision and convergence speed of the optimized RBFNN are superior compared with traditional RBFNN. © 2015 ICIC International.
