AB  - Genetic Algorithm (GA), an effective method to optimize combinational problem of optimization, has aroused intense interest, due to its flexibility, versatility and robustness. However, there exits some drawbacks such as premature, slow convergence and low efficiency. In order to overcome these shortcomings, a new GA by integration of chaotic initialization and dynamic quantum crossover is proposed. Application of this algorithm to the Traveling Salesman Problems (TSP) is performed. Simulation results have demonstrated the effectiveness and feasibility of the proposed method for the optimization problems. © 2014 ICIC International.
