AB  - The proceedings contain 163 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Materials Science and Engineering. The topics include: Research on mechanism in the SNCR DeNox process; investigation of low temperature sintering of low voltage varistor based on TiO2; direct immobilization of glucose oxidase on the hydrophilic copolymer support containing oxirane; ablation properties of ZrO2-MgO and Mo nozzle produced by plasma spray forming; identification of unknown sediment in water-reducer; zinc oxide production technology of distillation twice based on scrap miscellaneous zinc materials; effect of aluminium powder additives upon CO2 reactivity of electrolytic aluminium carbon anode with calcined anthracite; the effect of coating agent and preparation on the thermostability of coated potassium chlorate; dynamic recrystallization behavior of pure titanium; reaction heat of high alkali aluminosilicate glass batches in melting process; nano-rheology and its application in controlled-release fragrance nanocapsules suspensions; review of advanced technology of flue gas desulphurization; preparation and stability studies of a desulfurizer loaded on porous silica gel; preparation and properties of copper antibacterial silica; preparation and microstructure of exfoliated graphite with large expanding volume by two-step intercalation; wasted low grade iron ore with high phosphorus reuse for phosphate removal from aqueous solution by using a factorial design; university server room creep corrosion prevention; preparation and properties of porous poly(vinyl alcohol)/powdered activated carbon composite; dissolution of tungsten carbide in remanufacturing coating by plasma spray welding; research on the engineering properties of fly ash as backfill; the impact on the polypropylene matrix composites by the cutting size of the automotive interior decoration scrap; effect of pre-wetting super-light aggregate reinforced aerated concrete; effect of niobium on the morphology of n