AB  - It is easy for ant colony algorithm to fall into the local optimum and its convergent speed is slow in solving multiple energy-saving QoS constrained multicast routing problems. Through adjusting heuristic function, improving pheromone update rule and introducing of the fitness function to improve the traditional ant colony algorithm. According to the simulations, under the same experimental conditions, the basic ant algorithm converges to the local optimal cost of 87 in 12 iterations, and the multi-behaved ant colony algorithm in combination with quantum-behaved particle swarm optimization converges to the local optimal cost of 66 in 7 iterations. The algorithm converges to the global optimal cost of 62 in 10 iterations, which shows that the algorithm is better than the two previous algorithms. © Sila Science.
