AB  - The proceedings contain 99 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Material Science and Engineering, Nanomaterials and Nanostructure Synthesis and Properties, Nano Devices and System, Nano materials, Technologies for Applications, Circuits and Systems, Mechanical Engineering, and Industrial Electronics. The topics include: Nonlinear optical properties of biosilicate nanocomposite materials; nano photoelectric material structures-photonic crystals; the electrical characteristics induced by B+ doping of nanotube MOSFET; MeV electron-beam induced clusterization of platinum chloride on graphene for transparent conductive electrodes; polyurethane coating on a supporting layer of polymeric nanofibers; dielectric nano-systems with unique optical properties; the thermal properties of modified nano-silica with diluent/epoxy composites; interband electrooptical transitions in CdS/HgS/CdS cylindrical heterolayer-nanotube; atomic force microscope deposition assisted by electric field; Michelson interferometer for near infrared wavelengths; design and test of high-g MEMS accelerometer; growth and characterization of SnO2 nanostructures by vapor transport technique; electroluminescent quantum dot light-emitting diodes with ZnO and MoO3 carrier transport layers; refractive index sensor of V-shaped fiber microstructure fabricated by femtosecond laser; thermal design and analysis of VOx microbolometer; design, simulation and optimization of a new micro-structural gas sensor; constrained structural optimization of electro-thermal microactuator using double chromosome genetic evolution; analysis of construction material using SEM (Scanning Electron Microscope); dielectric properties of BaTi5O11 ceramics at microwave frequencies; electromagnetic field shielding fabrics with increased comfort properties; spray deposited thin films of tin-doped indium oxide for optoelectronic applications; polymer matrix on polymer dispersed liquid crystals electro-optical properties; co