AB  - The proceedings contain 141 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Metallic Materials, Ceramic and Inorganic Functional materials, Composite Materials, Aerospace Materials, Film Materials, Coating and Surface Technology, Environmental Functional Materials and Energy Materials, Mechanical, Thermal, Acoustical, Optical, Electric, Magnetic, Information and Optoelectronic Functional Materials, Biological, Macromolecule and Organic Functional Materials, Sensing and Smart Materials, Nanoscale Materials, Metamaterials, Electromagnetic Functional Materials, Fundamentals of Materials science, Materials Characterization Analysis and Simulation. The topics include: Characterization of the hot deformation behavior of a Al-Si alloy using processing maps; research on high strength hypoeutectic Al-Si alloy; the preparation and properties study of the zirconia dispersion-strengthened platinum materials; morphology and magnetic properties of NiCuZn ferrite synthesized by solid-molten salt method; effect of the precipitated second phase during aging on the damping capacity degradation behavior of M2052 alloy; microstructure and texture evolution law of Ti-IF steel for extra deep drawing during batch annealing process; classification of high quality carbon steel based on BP neural network; effect of microstructure of Mo-Cu alloy on the thermal expansion coefficient; research on effect factors of current efficiency in the process of sponge titanium production by electrolytic method; the study of fine tungsten rhenium thermocouple wires in the temperature measurement of the molten steel; application of magnetorheological fluid in bulge tests of sheet metal; a new type electrohydraulic servo valve based on magnetic shape memory alloy; simulation study of dynamic features during the isothermal relaxation processes in supercooled liquid and glassy Pb; synthesis of CuO flower-nanostructure via the hydrothermal method; influence of atomic defect on the deformation properties of nanowires subjected to uniaxial tension; the hydrothermal synthesis of BaTiO3 nanotubes arrays with good electrical property; the hydrothermal synthesis of ZrO2 nanoparticles and their optical absorption properties; memristive behaviors in Ag2S nano-particles assembly; characterization, photoluminescence and magnetic properties of SiC nanowires synthesized with nickel catalyst via microwave heating; controlled synthesis LaPO4 nanorods via a hydrothermal route; preparation of triangular silver nanoparticles using polyvinyl pyrrolidone with different concentration; low temperature degradation of Y-TZP ceramic for dental applications; fabrication of mullite fiber reinforced SiC porous ceramic; study on preparation and interlayer ion state of Fe/Ni pillared motmorillonite; controlled synthesis of Cu2O sheet-like particles by a simple solution method; the optimization of performance the new type of insulation wall materials based on waste foam glasses; a formaldehyde gas sensor based on zinc doped lanthanum ferrite; nanotip-induced ultrahigh pressure-sensitive cement-based composite and its pressure-sensitive characteristic model; effect of drawing speed on properties of the anti-reflective SiO2 film based on glass; preparation of straw superabsorbent composite material by microwave method; effects of particle size on microstructures and properties of Si/Al composites; effect of microwires diameters on the microwave properties of glass-coated microwires/dielectric composite; rapid lifetime evaluation of hybrid composite rods by creep behavior; research progress of diamond/Al composites; experimental studies and computer simulation of permeability determination of porous SiC preforms; analysis of moisture distribution within composite materials in hygrothermal environment; effect of a new coupling agent on mechanical properties of domestic high-modulus carbon fiber/cyanate composites; the super capacitor with nanosic film electrode; thin film thermocouples for surface temperature measurement of turbine blade; influence of sputtering power on molybdenum-doped zinc oxide films grown by RF magnetron sputtering; preparation and photocatalyst of Ce/Zn composite oxide; perfect absorber based on mie dielectric metamaterials; metamaterials with zero phase delay; effects of Si spacer-layer on the structure of Ge/Si quantum dots bilayers grown by ion beam sputtering; dielectric properties of Al2O3 nanofibers/epoxy resin nanocomposites; synthesis and characterization of luminescent TiO2/polymer nanocomposites; failure analysis and research progress of resurfacing welding material of coal mill roller; formation mechanism and photocatalytic properties of bismuth vanadate; an ultraviolent-enhanced response solar cell and tunneling effect; research in effects of environmentally-friendly carbon black masterbatch powder rubber; the day-and-night solar lighting system; photocatalytic water splitting and photocatalytic degradation in aqueous GdVO4 suspensions under simulated solar irradiation; electrochemical performance of graphene nanosheets as electrode material for supercapacitors; the application of electromagnetic metamaterials for wireless power transfer; construction of three-dimensional scaffold for tissue engineered heart valves; advances in biomaterial's modification and thrombosis inhibition; degradation modeling research of biodegradable tissue engineering scaffold; post-processing of chitosan based nanofibers prepared by electrospinning; experimental research on the performance of PSA and other fiber filter; study on synthesis and property of anti-salt super absorbent resin; the preparation and characterization of spherical cellulose aerogels with core-shell structure; synthesis of super absorbent resin from starch/bentonite; dielectrophoresis response and manipulation of silica and its application to micro/nanosensors; acoustic properties of loose and consolidated nonmetal particles from waste printed circuit boards; research on pr