AB  - The proceedings contain 108 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Management engineering, Manufacturing Engineering and Modeling, System Modeling and Simulation, Automation Control and Applications, Materials Science and Engineering, Computer Science and Logistics Engineering, Sensor and the Internet of Things, Computer Science and Logistics Engineering, Engineering and Management, Mechanical Science and Engineering. The topics include: The preparation of water-solution Mn-Doped ZnS quantum dots; studies on surface hydroxypropylation and swellability of bacterial cellulose; effect of chemisorptions on wetting property in TiO nanosheet film; numerical studies on effect of interpass time on distortion and residual stresses in multipass welding; a delamination factor prediction model for drilling of composite materials; research on tensile strength in the ultrasonic welding joint of T-Type wood-plastic composites components; preparation, characterization of Cu nanowires and their tribological property in liquid paraffin; study of magnetism of two-dimensional ferromagnetic graphene; machining FEM model of unidirectional carbon fiber reinforced laminate; the research on the disperse form of PEO fiber by electrostatic spinning method; the hydraulic characteristics of slope flow; evaluation of tobacco mixing uniformity based on projection pursuit; reasonably water injection time about abnormal pressure of low permeability reservoir; finite element stress analysis of a 600 MW supercritical boiler superheater outlet header; a dual-band LTCC antenna with cross circuitous structure; seismic vulnerability assessment of multistory timber braced frame traditional masonry structures; analysis of land use changes on groundwater dynamics; hand-motion recognition system using directional patterns of gyroscope for smart device control; optimization method of wavefront reconstruction based on spatial light modulator; evaluation of sensorial qualities of fruit wines by kohonen neural network; numerical simulation of meso-mechanism of liquefaction in saturated stratified silty sands; experimental research on chloride-induced service life of sturctures under loading capacity criterion; fast test and evaluation method for online dynamic performances of feed drive system of CNC machine tool; model for yarn transport systems; parameter modeling method for aeroengine virtual testing system; simulation and optimization of a biscuit processing production in an industrial scale by use of MLP and RBF neuro fuzzy network; abrasion simulation of a reciprocating seal; theory of yarn dynamics during unwinding from packages; time-history response analysis of jacket offshore platform due to water level variation and safety of structural members; support vector regression based nonlinear model reference adaptive control; investigation of performance of scramjet combustion used kerosene with clean air; an authentication structure across trust domains; towards web service discovery based on context-aware; digital forensic technology of solaris; optimal order picking in carousels storage system; expressway event management expert system based on ontology and rule reasoning; unified information modeling for achieving high-performance information sharing in the information grid; the design of inter-regional fire and rescue mobilization system; network manufacturing technology based on cloud computing; a new document representation using a unified graph to document similarity search; model checking of constraint-based workflow based on linear temporal logic; improvement and research of lean production in car-seat assembly line; establishing a marketing plan for nowdar company applying a taxonomy method; performance assessment for digital convergence development in Taiwan; a graph partition model for cross docking schedule problem developed mechanism and solutions to modern eco-logistics industry in China; the comparative analysis of international competitiveness on China's peanut industry; a game theory based analysis of the tacit knowledge sharing and incentive mechanism; tactic of supply chain coordination when the freight cost of unit product is sensitive to lot size.
