TI  - Performance optimization and instability study in ring cavity quantum cascade lasers
PY  - 2015
T2  - IEEE Journal of Quantum Electronics
VL  - 51
IS  - 1
C7  - 6962893
DO  - 10.1109/JQE.2014.2373171
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-84919481359&doi=10.1109%2fJQE.2014.2373171&partnerID=40&md5=dff9ea8c31ef036d69a1529333dfd11f
AB  - An optimization study of quantum cascade lasers (QCLs) considering the laser instability condition is performed. To model current transport, the Pauli master equation is solved using a Monte Carlo approach. The effects of saturable absorber and pumping strength on the instability threshold are investigated. A particle swarm optimization algorithm is applied to increase the laser optical gain. A large optical gain below the instability threshold is achieved for optimized QCL designs. To analyze the optimized structure, a numerical calculation based on the Maxwell-Bloch equations is performed. The results indicate side-mode instabilities due to Risken-Nummedal-Graham-Haken-like instability. © 2014 IEEE.
