AB  - The proceedings contain 20 papers. The topics discussed include: surface phenomena and parameters of crystal growth: simple basics; from initial to late stages of epitaxial thin film growth: STM analysis and atomistic or coarse-grained modeling; physical mechanisms of crystal growth modification by biomolecules; nucleation of crystals in solution; metal organic vapor phase growth of complex semiconductor alloys; crystal growth of semiconductor bulk crystals; crystal morphology; chirality change by grinding crystals in solution; modeling and bulk crystal growth processes: what is to be learned?; phase-field simulations of crystal growth; optimization and modeling of photovoltaic silicon crystallization processes; a brief introduction to phase field method; developments in interferometric techniques for in-situ observation of surface kinetics of crystals in solutions and three-dimensional analysis of transport phenomena; and nanoepitaxy in the presence of lattice strain: quantum dots and strain engineering of nanomembranes in the silicon model system.
