AB  - The problem of minimum cost multicast tree satisfying bandwidth request and delay-constraint in communication network is a NP-complete problem. It is difficult to be solved by traditional methods. At present, heuristic methods (such as GA ) are used. In this paper, an approach based on parallel quantum genetic algorithm (PQGA) is proposed to solve QoS (quality of service) multicast routing. In this algorithm, each subpopulation evolves independently and concurrently, and prematurity and partial convergence are avoided by information exchange among neighboring subpopulations. In addition a new dynamic rotating angle adjustment policy is proposed, leading to better seed population diversity and global optimization capability of the algorithm. The simulation results have shown that PQGA has better performance than QGA with static rotating angle and GA.
