AB  - The proceedings contain 256 papers. The topics discussed included: electrospray wings for nanoscale elephants; nanostructured optics and optoelectronics for dense interconnects; modeling and simulation of nanoscale self-assembly structure; a coupled simulation and optimization approach to nanodevice fabrication with minimization of electrical characteristics fluctuation; a study of the performance of ballistic nanoscale MOSFETs using classical and quantum ballistic transport models; electronic properties of silicon nanowires: confined phonons and surface roughness; an efficient and symbolic model for charge densities in ballistic carbon nanotube FETs; modeling and simulation of nanoscale self-assembly structures; a novel design and simulation of resonant cavity enhanced (RCE) conjugated quantum well infrared photodectors (C-QWIP) using the finite difference time domain (FDTD) method.
