AB  - The novel types of symmetry-broken mesoscopic semiconductor structures were investigated. The phenomena of ballistic rectification could be understood within the framework of different transport regimes. The opposite sign of the output voltage as compared to the prediction was observed. Demonstrating the basic principle upon which the rectification was based and the asymmetry of the voltage drop in a quasiclassical wire, the experiments were explained as being caused by the interplay of quasiclassical ballistic and classical transport.
