AB  - The proceedings contain 192 papers. The topics discussed include: picosecond pulses from mode - locked quantum well semiconductor lasers; progress report on the development of a coulomb imaging experiment; single- and multiple -pulse femtosecond laser irradiation of iron, copper, and aluminum; fabrication and subpicosecond photoresponse of a noval LT-GaAs photoconductive switch; production of models of the international space station elements from 3D laser images; tracking targets on the international space station using a laser scanner; pre -launch calibration of the advanced camera for surveys; simulation and optimization of the SWIFT stratospheric wind interferometer for transport studies on GCOM -AI; design of a mechanically actuated reconfigurable slitmask for the NGST near IR spectrograph; and optical design considerations for astronomical and space applications.
