AB  - The design and optimization of complex nanoscale electron devices by simulations with quantum transport models were discussed. The simulation models included in the device simulator SIMBA were the quantum drift diffusion and quantum hydrodynamic models. With the quantum hydrodynamic model, it is possible to consider quantum mechanical effects, such as resonant tunneling of electrons and holes through potential barriers. Poisson equation, continuity equations and the transport equations without the temperature gradient were used to describe quantum drift diffusions processes and denoted as quantum drift diffusion model. Numerical 2D-simulation results of nanoscale devices such as quantum wires were also presented.
