AB  - In this paper, the optimization of organic light emitting diode (OLED) with respect to the change of thickness is presented. It is performed by response surface model generated from D-optimal design. First, six performance indexes called current efficiency, power efficiency, quantum efficiency, luminance and color coordinates of three colors (red, green, and blue) are optimized for achieving the target color coordinates of white (x=0.27, y=0.35) by using white coordinate equations. Next, these performance indexes are used to explore and calculate the optimal thickness of organic light emitting diode that includes hole injection layer, hole transport layer, emission layer, electron transport layer, electron injection layer and cathode.
